entries.femaleVariant: Kiroshi optics. Best I've got and should be about right under the circumstances.
[Sit]
Need some new kit – but tools, not toys, Vik. Time I bumped up my sights and got a grip.
Looking to upgrade.
Chair, please. Siddown, relax.
The Dexter DeShawn? Heheh, well, that is something. But lemme guess – hasn't paid you yet.
Pay you once the job's done.
Quit cryin', Vik, I'll bring you the eddies later, with interest. You know I will.
entries.maleVariant: Quit cryin', Vik. I'll bring you the eddies later. With interest. You know I will.

entries.femaleVariant: Vik, shit's gettin' real. Got a job from Dex DeShawn – hittin' the major leagues. Need tech that can perform.
Vik... this job's my golden ticket. I'm talkin' life changing. Without the right tech, I…
entries.maleVariant: Vik, this job's my golden ticket. I'm talkin' life changin'. Without gettin' the right tech, I…

entries.femaleVariant: Take my car in exchange.
MK1, like I said. Decent enough scanner. Displays data on your cornea. Cherry on the top's a built-in external lens disruptor.
Hmm... This should do the trick. Talks to Kiroshi tech, too.
OK, let's test this, see the magic in action. Linking you in.
I'm ready. Carve away.
Better than ever.
Whoa, this is fantastic, Vik.
Now, a bit of anesthetic and I can start cutting.
Haha, beautiful. Time for the scanner.
Feels like I'm at the dentist's.
Play by play, though? Really, doc? Makes you sound like a dentist – always goin' on and on…
Don't be mean, now. 'Member, I'm old. I got a shaky, 'ganic hand. Could slip.
Feel anything?
Now draw your weapon. You should see your ammo count and a brand new sight.
Thanks, Vik.
Shit, Viktor, not bad. I dunno what to say.
Say you'll take this and remember the dosage. Two whiffs now and another two in an hour.
[Stand] Thanks, Vik. You're the best.
What's this?
What'm I lookin' at?
You're the best, Vik. I owe you.
A mild stim. Should boost neurotransmission in the short term and muffle some of the side effects while the implant takes.
Hahahaha… Go on, kid. Show 'em what you're made of.
Viky, spry as ever, you old ripper. Good to see you.
entries.maleVariant: Viky, spry as ever, you old ripper. It's good to see you.

entries.femaleVariant: Good to see you too, V. It's been a while. To what do I owe the pleasure today?
Eeexcellent. Let's do this.
Heh. Lay that major league arm of yours right here.
It might take you a few seconds to adjust, but… first time's rarely the charm, with anything, really. Scanner should eventually sync with your thought processes an' read your intentions.
Heheheheh. Really? Now? Finally?
And once you hit the big leagues, don't forget where you came from.
[Place arm]
Just like that. Thanks.
Heheheheh. It oughta work like a charm…
Lights out for a minute, all right?
You might feel a little discomfort at first. Blurred vision, low contrast, glitches…
Malone drops his guard. Hah – you can see the fatigue on him. It's-it's-it's really startin' to weigh him down, startin' to take over!
Oh-ho-hoh! That musta hurt! Wow! Malone's in the corner, he's lookin' for a way out. Just-just lookin' for a breather, here! Tha-- That was the hardest punch of the round, no doubt!
Malone is on the ropes! Malone is in trouble! And... there's the end of the round! Saved by the bell!
Hernandez keepin' him cornered with excellent footwork, those Zetatech calves of his just shining!
Hernandez pounces on the chance, comin' in with a couple of hooks! Gainin' the upper hand pretty darn quickly!
Now jack in.
That's it?
What about the virus?
You peruse and choose while I scan. See what's goin' on inside.
[Jack in]
Well, how's it look? Feel all right to you?
Heard of Dexter DeShawn?
[Draw weapon]
Kiroshi! That's top-shelf tech.
What's new in the life of Viktor?
Nothing.
OK, let's test this, see the magic in action. Linking you in.
You might feel a little discomfort at first. Blurred vision, low contrast, glitches…
Well, how's it look? Feel all right to you?
Just like that. Thanks.
Now, a bit of anesthetic and I can start cutting.
Feel anything?
Thanks again, Vik, you're the best. I owe you.
Hahahaha… Go on, kid. Show 'em what you're made of.
And once you hit the big leagues, don't forget where you came from.
Last gig – had to jack into a client's neurosocket… Think I mighta gotten spiked.
Experiencing migraines, nausea, hypersensitivity to bright lights?
Whole kit and kaboodle.
All right, kid. We'll sort you out in a flash. 'Sides that, how're things?
Met a new fixer, gave me a job. Name's Dexter DeShawn.
entries.maleVariant: Met a new fixer, he gave me a job. Name's Dexter DeShawn.

entries.femaleVariant: Known quantity, from the Afterlife. No denying you're movin' up…
But? Somethin' you're not tellin' me, Vik?
entries.maleVariant: But? Something you're not tellin' me, Vik?

entries.femaleVariant: Keep your guard up, that's all. I've heard some things about Dex. He's not as "chill" as he makes himself out to be.
Hmm...
Last time, you hear?
My wheels – give 'em to you as collateral. Fifty-eight Quadra Turbo-R series.
Hmm... Fifty-eight, you say? Black?
As a moonless night.
Don't have the heart to take your baby. Pay me when the job's done.
Same as always – don't feel a thing.
Y'ask me that every time, you know. Not as if things're gonna be any different today.
entries.maleVariant: Y'ask me that every time, you know? Not as if things're gonna be any different today.

entries.femaleVariant: Sure thing, kid, I mean… not like there's any risk of a stroke or paralysis. But... heh, what do I know? I'm just a doctor…
That's what I thought.
Seen more dramatic improvements before…
Patience, kid. Give it a minute. Time for the scanner.
How 'bout the neurovirus, from the last job? Can ya check it?
Done and gone while we were puttin' in your implant. Ran a full sweep on your soft and circuits. Zapped the critter. You're certified bug-free.
In layman's terms, any surveillance cam'll capture your face as a blur. Now just remember, your body'll still show up as crystal clear.
So… what's new in the life of Viktor Vektor?
Heh. Er, if I'm bein' honest? Not much. An' that's fine with me.
I used to live in a world where all that mattered was who's who, what's what and how's why.
And what happened?
One day I just dropped it and never looked back. I'll never be a legend in this town... but been sleeping nights ever since.
Kiroshi? Whoa! Vik, nothing tops that on the market.
entries.maleVariant: Kiroshi? Whoa! Vik, nothin' tops that on the market.

entries.femaleVariant: Hm. Sounds like it could come in handy, then.
Gave you my word I'd pay you back, but this... might be too rich for my blood.
We'll work something out. Right now, I'm just out to make sure you get back in one piece – eddies in hand.
I also injected an NCPD file search.
Run into any ne'er-do-wells, heh, you'll know exactly what they ne'er-did-well.
Not yet, but I'm good for the eddies anyway. Gotta invest in not fuckin' up this gig.
entries.maleVariant: Not yet, but I'm good for the eddies anyway. I gotta invest in not fuckin' up this gig.

entries.femaleVariant: Got the money.
[Jack in]
[Open] Hey, Viktor.
